  "texts": [
    "By (a), h p (h(y ′) ∧ x) ⊑ ′ h p (h(y ′)), and by (b), h p (h(y ′)) ⊑ ′ y ′, so h p (h(y ′) ∧ x) ⊑ ′ y ′.",
    "Third, we claim that y ′ ⊑ ′ h p (h(y ′) ∧ x).",
    "By definition of h p, it suffices to show that y ′ ⊑ x ′ for all x ′ ∈ A ′ p such that h(y ′) ∧ x ⊑ h(x ′).",
    "From h(y ′) ∧ x ⊑ h(x ′), we have x ⊑ -h(y ′) ∨ h(x ′) and hence x ⊑ h(-y ′ ∨ x ′), which by (a) and (b) implies h p (x) ⊑ ′ h p (h(-y ′ ∨ x ′)) ⊑ -y ′ ∨ x ′.",
    "Then since y ′ ⊑ ′ h p (x), it follows that y ′ ⊑ ′ x ′, as desired."
